      <section id="#baggage">
        <div class="container-fluid p-0">
          <div class="row">
            <div class="col-12 text-center">
              <h2 class="fw-bold display-6 word py-3 font1">Baggage Allowance</h2>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="row d-flex flex-row align-items-center">
            <div class="col-12 col-lg-6">
              <img src="./Images/Baggage.jpg" class="card-img-top" alt="...">
            </div>
            <div class="col-12 col-lg-6 font7">
              <p>1.Checked Baggage: Airlines typically allow passengers to check one or more bags depending on their ticket class and destination</p>
              <p>2.Weight Limit: Each checked bag usually has a weight limit, commonly ranging from 20 to 30 kilograms (44 to 66 pounds) per bag.</p>
              <p>3.Size Restrictions: Checked bags must usually adhere to specific size dimensions, often around 158 cm (62 inches) in total (length + width + height).</p>
              <p>4.Carry-On Bags: Passengers are usually allowed one carry-on bag and sometimes a personal item such as a purse or laptop bag.</p>
              <p>5.Weight and Size Limits for Carry-Ons: Carry-on bags typically have weight limits of around 7 to 10 kilograms (15 to 22 pounds) and size restrictions, usually around 55 x 40 x 20 cm (22 x 16 x 8 inches).</p>
              <p>6.Excess Baggage Fees: Airlines may charge fees for baggage that exceeds the allowed weight or size limits.</p>
              <p>7.Special Items: Some items like sports equipment, musical instruments, and pets may have specific rules or require additional fees.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div><!--end of contianer-fluid-->
      </section><!--end of baggage section-->

      <section>
